00:43:50,129 --> 00:43:51,547
How can you be sure?

507
00:43:52,506 --> 00:43:58,887
There's a voice inside me,
telling me what I have to do.

508
00:43:59,346 --> 00:44:01,890
And it's telling me I need you.

509
00:44:21,493 --> 00:44:22,494
Shit.

510
00:44:38,052 --> 00:44:39,386
They have Logan.

511
00:44:43,307 --> 00:44:44,516
Help me.

512
00:44:45,267 --> 00:44:46,352
Help me.

513
00:44:49,605 --> 00:44:50,814
No.

514
00:44:55,611 --> 00:44:56,904
No more pretending.

515
00:45:08,290 --> 00:45:12,419
I thought you had no appetite
for war, boy.

516
00:45:12,711 --> 00:45:16,465
This is a declaration of war.

517
00:45:20,260 --> 00:45:21,720
El Lazo set us up.

518
00:45:21,970 --> 00:45:23,305
We can find him for you.

519
00:45:23,472 --> 00:45:26,600
You can find him for us
by joining him in hell.

520
00:45:30,604 --> 00:45:31,688
Dolores, run!

521
00:45:45,786 --> 00:45:46,912
Dolores?

522
00:46:00,634 --> 00:46:02,177
How did you do that?

523
00:46:02,845 --> 00:46:07,141
You said people come here
to change the story of their lives.

524
00:46:10,561 --> 00:46:13,730
I imagined a story
where I didn't have to be the damsel.

525
00:46:17,359 --> 00:46:20,612
Now that train is our only chance
of making it out of here alive.

526
00:46:53,812 --> 00:46:55,147
Motherfuckers.

527
00:47:08,744 --> 00:47:12,998
You pull that trigger,
we'll all go up in a ball of hellfire.

528
00:47:13,248 --> 00:47:15,417
So, why don't you loosen your grip a mite?

529
00:47:23,425 --> 00:47:24,468
It's okay.

530
00:47:26,136 --> 00:47:27,262
I don't trust him.

531
00:47:27,429 --> 00:47:29,973
Which is the first step
to truly knowing me.

532
00:47:31,099 --> 00:47:32,768
Give me your gun, El Lazo.

533
00:47:38,649 --> 00:47:42,653
Now that we're all friends,
you can call me Lawrence.

534
00:47:43,654 --> 00:47:46,698
Now, why don't we settle in.
It's a long ride to the front.

535
00:47:58,335 --> 00:48:00,045
<i>You want a sip of this swill?</i>

536
00:48:04,466 --> 00:48:06,885
<i>Don't worry, it ain't nitro.</i>

537
00:48:15,310 --> 00:48:16,520
I'm coming.

538
00:48:37,249 --> 00:48:39,668
The girls are a little worn out,
but I can rouse one.

539
00:48:40,002 --> 00:48:41,378
You boys want some company?

540
00:48:41,545 --> 00:48:43,005
No. Just whiskey.

541
00:48:50,679 --> 00:48:53,849
Lawrence's donation must be running low.

542
00:48:54,683 --> 00:48:56,602
But we're short on time.

543
00:48:56,852 --> 00:48:58,604
You need to buck up, Teddy.

544
00:49:02,024 --> 00:49:04,359
<i>I told you, no company.</i>

545
00:49:05,902 --> 00:49:11,533
Thought I might join you, anyway,
as I never like to drink alone.

546
00:49:13,201 --> 00:49:16,913
Well, isn't this a rare honor?

547
00:49:18,040 --> 00:49:20,709
Teddy, you know who this is?

548
00:49:23,045 --> 00:49:24,630
Can't say that I do.

549
00:49:24,880 --> 00:49:27,716
Everything good
that has ever happened in your life,

550
00:49:27,924 --> 00:49:32,304
and everything rotten,
this is the man you have to thank.

551
00:49:35,891 --> 00:49:37,434
How am I doing, Robert?

552
00:49:38,477 --> 00:49:40,646
Any closer to finding
what I'm looking for?

553
00:49:40,812 --> 00:49:43,106
And what is that, exactly?

554
00:49:44,399 --> 00:49:46,234
<i>We're looking for a man named Wyatt.</i>

555
00:49:46,735 --> 00:49:50,072
Killed a rancher back in Sweetwater,
took his daughter.

556
00:49:52,574 --> 00:49:54,785
That last part doesn't sound familiar.

557
00:49:55,410 --> 00:49:58,372
Figured your stories
could use a little embellishment.

558
00:49:59,122 --> 00:50:03,251
You know, I always felt this place
was missing a real villain,

559
00:50:03,502 --> 00:50:06,421
hence my humble contribution.

560
00:50:08,256 --> 00:50:12,636
I admit, I lack the imagination
to even conceive of someone like you.

561
00:50:13,762 --> 00:50:16,848
The urgency, however,
doesn't quite fit the character.

562
00:50:17,432 --> 00:50:19,976
It betrays a certain anxiety.

563
00:50:22,729 --> 00:50:27,442
Now, Wyatt, on the other hand,
that's something new.

564
00:50:28,068 --> 00:50:31,279
Is he just another stooge for the tourists
to mount on their wall at home,

565
00:50:31,446 --> 00:50:34,282
or have you finally made
a worthy adversary?

566
00:50:35,742 --> 00:50:40,455
Someone to stop me
from finding the center of the maze.

567
00:50:42,332 --> 00:50:44,793
And what is it
you're hoping to find there?

568
00:50:47,963 --> 00:50:49,965
You know why you exist, Teddy?

569
00:50:51,007 --> 00:50:54,803
The world out there,
the one you'll never see,

570
00:50:55,804 --> 00:50:57,389
is one of plenty.

571
00:50:57,848 --> 00:51:00,976
A fat, soft teat
people cling to their entire life.

572
00:51:01,727 --> 00:51:04,396
Every need taken care of,

573
00:51:04,646 --> 00:51:05,814
except one.

574
00:51:07,149 --> 00:51:08,316
Purpose.

575
00:51:09,401 --> 00:51:10,652
Meaning.

576
00:51:11,528 --> 00:51:13,321
So, they come here.

577
00:51:13,488 --> 00:51:16,074
They can be a little scared,
a little thrilled,

578
00:51:16,241 --> 00:51:18,326
enjoy some sweetly affirmative bullshit,

579
00:51:18,493 --> 00:51:21,538
and then they take a fucking picture
and they go back home.

580
00:51:22,831 --> 00:51:26,209
But I think there's a deeper meaning

581
00:51:26,376 --> 00:51:28,503
hiding under all that.

582
00:51:28,837 --> 00:51:33,216
Something that the person
who created it wanted to express.

583
00:51:36,344 --> 00:51:38,138
Something true.

584
00:51:40,140 --> 00:51:42,851
Well, if you're looking
for the moral of the story,

585
00:51:43,018 --> 00:51:44,311
you could quite simply ask.

586
00:51:44,728 --> 00:51:47,022
I'd need a shovel.

587
00:51:47,189 --> 00:51:50,233
The man I'd be asking died 35 years ago.

588
00:51:50,484 --> 00:51:52,402
Almost took this place with him.

589
00:51:52,652 --> 00:51:56,198
Almost, but not quite. Thanks to me.

590
00:51:56,865 --> 00:52:00,035
Well, maybe he left something behind.

591
00:52:02,871 --> 00:52:07,083
I wonder what I would find
if I opened you up.

592
00:52:15,550 --> 00:52:19,888
Even at death's door,
you're still a loyal pet.

593
00:52:27,270 --> 00:52:28,980
Is that why you came here, Robert?

594
00:52:30,106 --> 00:52:32,067
To try to talk me out of it?

595
00:52:32,484 --> 00:52:34,402
On the contrary.

596
00:52:34,986 --> 00:52:39,407
Far be it from me to get in the way
of a voyage of self-discovery.

597
00:52:50,961 --> 00:52:52,212
Mr. Flood.

598
00:52:52,379 --> 00:52:57,801
We must look back and smile
at perils past, mustn't we?

599
00:53:10,063 --> 00:53:13,900
We should get back on the road.
Time's a-wasting.

600
00:55:07,055 --> 00:55:08,556
<i>Hello, Felix.</i>

601
00:55:12,227 --> 00:55:14,604
It's time you and I had a chat.

